1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,600
I bring you greetings from the University Baptist Church in Palm Desert, one of our

2
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:12,080
sister churches, and a few of them walked up, and now their name escapes me. I wrote

3
00:00:12,080 --> 00:00:16,400
it down, but they've said, oh, is such and such still there? And they bring greetings

4
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:21,920
to you, so I'm just excited to be worshiping with them, and they're excited for what God

5
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:24,700
is doing here, so greetings from the Palm Desert Church.

6
00:00:25,860 --> 00:00:29,480
Well, as we finish or come close to the end of our series, I'd like to share from the

7
00:00:29,480 --> 00:00:35,900
book, The Healing of Memories, David Siemens tells an interesting story about the reality

8
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:43,150
at the end of World War II. The Japanese government at that time faced a massive problem

9
00:00:43,150 --> 00:00:50,200
because even though the peace documents had been signed, there were thousands of Japanese soldiers

10
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:58,560
in the mountains and the jungles in the Pacific that didn't know the war was over. How do you

11
00:00:58,560 --> 00:01:04,320
bring them all back in? How do you teach them that we're done? In fact, not only was it difficult

12
00:01:04,320 --> 00:01:09,560
because they didn't know the war was over, they were brainwashed into thinking that if they

13
00:01:09,560 --> 00:01:16,510
surrendered to the American troops, horrible, horrible things would be done unto them. And so

14
00:01:16,510 --> 00:01:24,490
they remained hidden, hiding in the caves in the jungles. Well, the emperor made a speech explaining

15
00:01:24,490 --> 00:01:31,090
the situation and pleading to the men to come home, and it was broadcast by radio, and it

16
00:01:31,090 --> 00:01:36,450
was recorded, and they played it on recording devices and boomed it out into the jungles.

17
00:01:37,420 --> 00:01:39,420
In essence, it's all right.

18
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:45,840
And because it came in the voice of the emperor, it began to work.

19
00:01:46,300 --> 00:01:50,480
As they heard the trusted voice, they began to come out.

20
00:01:52,470 --> 00:01:53,490
It took a while.

21
00:01:54,190 --> 00:01:55,210
There were stragglers.

22
00:01:55,210 --> 00:02:00,790
It took a few months, but they got all of them out, they thought.

23
00:02:02,470 --> 00:02:03,170
But there was one.

24
00:02:04,670 --> 00:02:10,550
There was one who stayed hidden until 1974.

25
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:21,120
29 years after the war was over, he finally came out of hiding.

26
00:02:22,960 --> 00:02:27,260
Japan and the United States of America had been rebuilding the relationship

27
00:02:27,260 --> 00:02:31,620
and forging economic ties and moving on with life.

28
00:02:32,340 --> 00:02:37,580
But one man gave up 29 years of his life in hiding.

29
00:02:37,580 --> 00:02:45,890
When they asked him why he waited, he said it was because he was afraid.

30
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:47,460
He was afraid.

31
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:56,600
Trapped by 29 years of fear, not by an invading army, but by fear.

32
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:05,720
Friends, we can be hidden and trapped by fear ourselves.

33
00:03:06,810 --> 00:03:11,290
We can completely miss out on life because of fear.

34
00:03:11,890 --> 00:03:16,490
We can miss out on what God would have for us because of fear.

35
00:03:16,890 --> 00:03:24,420
Like the couple in today's drama, we can get locked into patterns and cycles of living

36
00:03:24,420 --> 00:03:28,020
that would keep us in a comfort zone

37
00:03:28,020 --> 00:03:31,790
that holds us back from really living

38
00:03:31,790 --> 00:03:34,630
and accomplishing what God would have for us.

39
00:03:36,660 --> 00:03:40,380
They got stuck by the comfort of a couch.

40
00:03:45,330 --> 00:03:47,950
The Houston Chronicle in the early part of the 90s

41
00:03:47,950 --> 00:03:51,870
carried a story about a jilted English bride

42
00:03:51,870 --> 00:03:53,830
from Reading, England.

43
00:03:55,340 --> 00:03:57,140
This was an amazing story to me.

44
00:03:57,140 --> 00:03:58,280
I almost didn't believe it,

45
00:03:58,420 --> 00:04:00,760
but the source was right

46
00:04:00,760 --> 00:04:10,800
and she lived in her garden for 35 years after being abandoned by her fiancé at the altar.

47
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,080
It's a tragic story.

48
00:04:14,710 --> 00:04:17,850
She refused to go back into her home.

49
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:25,770
And so she began to build a shelter in her garden from trees and twigs and brightly colored umbrellas

50
00:04:25,770 --> 00:04:29,110
and furnished it with car seats and briefcases.

51
00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:37,300
She left that house exactly as it was on the day she was to be married.

52
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:44,490
And she died at the age of 70, 35 years living in the garden.

53
00:04:46,210 --> 00:04:47,850
A pastor commented, and I quote,

54
00:04:47,850 --> 00:04:56,070
She lived and died in a comfort zone designed to protect her from her emotional pain.

55
00:04:57,480 --> 00:05:01,880
She had gotten stuck on a mistake and was not able to move beyond it.

56
00:05:02,830 --> 00:05:05,890
Her homemade hovel didn't look like much of a comfort zone,

57
00:05:07,190 --> 00:05:09,370
but that's the way comfort zones are.

58
00:05:10,540 --> 00:05:12,660
To the owner, it looks wonderful,

59
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,500
but to the outside observer,

60
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:18,080
our comfort zones may not look so great.

61
00:05:19,080 --> 00:05:20,780
We get comfortable with things

62
00:05:20,780 --> 00:05:23,500
that ought not to feel comfortable,

63
00:05:24,970 --> 00:05:29,270
and Jesus calls us out of those comfort zones.

64
00:05:29,670 --> 00:05:31,650
He calls us to change.

65
00:05:31,650 --> 00:05:39,650
You cannot move out of your comfort zones unless you're willing to make mistakes and learn to move beyond them.

66
00:05:41,900 --> 00:05:43,580
Comfort zones are comfortable, aren't they?

67
00:05:44,810 --> 00:05:47,350
We do life in predictable ways.

68
00:05:47,850 --> 00:05:50,010
We do relationships in safe manners.

69
00:05:50,150 --> 00:05:52,250
We do ministry in safe, predictable ways.

70
00:05:52,770 --> 00:05:58,660
Let's be honest, we sit every Sunday in the same places, most of you.

71
00:06:00,670 --> 00:06:04,390
I was even tempted to stand up and actually shuffle you all around.

72
00:06:04,390 --> 00:06:06,010
I won't do that this morning.

73
00:06:07,420 --> 00:06:10,540
But wouldn't that be interesting, to look at it from a different point of view?

74
00:06:13,770 --> 00:06:18,810
Sometimes patterns can be the biggest obstacles to fulfilling God-given dreams.

75
00:06:19,810 --> 00:06:24,270
When I was brand new around here, first few weeks, someone actually said to me,

76
00:06:24,590 --> 00:06:30,030
we want you, pastor, to lead us and grow us, but don't make any changes to the church or the service

77
00:06:30,030 --> 00:06:32,030
because we like it the way it is.

78
00:06:34,020 --> 00:06:35,640
Lead us, but don't touch anything.

79
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:37,620
It's a true story.

80
00:06:39,820 --> 00:06:41,540
But friends, healthy churches, however,

81
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:44,460
are always changing and growing and facing new challenges.

82
00:06:45,140 --> 00:06:48,020
And healthy churches are filled with healthy believers

83
00:06:48,020 --> 00:06:50,720
who live to do God's will,

84
00:06:51,260 --> 00:06:53,580
even if that means growing personally

85
00:06:53,580 --> 00:06:57,000
and stretching our comfort zones

86
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:59,780
or stepping out of them altogether.

87
00:07:00,930 --> 00:07:01,910
Which one are you?

88
00:07:01,910 --> 00:07:05,610
Are you ready to take risks with God?

89
00:07:05,610 --> 00:07:10,440
or do you like life just as it is?

90
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:16,820
And would you like to be in that first category that I listed

91
00:07:16,820 --> 00:07:21,440
of one who's ready to take risks with God?

92
00:07:22,430 --> 00:07:24,950
We've been talking about daring to dream again

93
00:07:24,950 --> 00:07:28,330
and overcoming barriers that would hold us back.

94
00:07:29,220 --> 00:07:32,220
And one of the barriers that can hold us back from dreaming

95
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:34,760
and pursuing God's dreams for us

96
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:39,420
is our reluctance to leave our comfort zones.

97
00:07:40,710 --> 00:07:44,110
We just like things the way they are.

98
00:07:46,180 --> 00:07:48,860
And we can let God go right on by.

99
00:07:51,950 --> 00:07:55,010
If you are in a relationship with God this morning,

100
00:07:55,510 --> 00:08:02,650
chances are that He is prodding you to grow and to change in some area of your life.

101
00:08:03,010 --> 00:08:05,010
I don't know what that is necessarily,

102
00:08:05,010 --> 00:08:10,350
but chances are he's speaking and pushing and growing and wanting to stretch you.

103
00:08:10,930 --> 00:08:14,510
That's a major part of our journey with God.

104
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:18,200
And as we've been talking about over the last several weeks,

105
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:26,440
God is leading many of you to dream again and to pursue those dreams for God.

106
00:08:29,950 --> 00:08:34,960
I'd like for you to consider a young woman that presents a dream to her.

107
00:08:35,460 --> 00:08:38,780
We usually look at her at Christmas.

108
00:08:39,040 --> 00:08:43,640
But her story fits in August as well.

109
00:08:44,930 --> 00:08:47,090
So I take you this morning to Luke chapter 1.

110
00:08:50,770 --> 00:08:56,310
In the sixth month of Elizabeth's pregnancy, God sent the angel Gabriel to Nazareth,

111
00:08:56,850 --> 00:09:00,770
a village in Galilee, to a virgin named Mary.

112
00:09:02,100 --> 00:09:06,660
She was engaged to be married to a man named Joseph, a descendant of King David.

113
00:09:07,300 --> 00:09:09,240
And Gabriel appeared to her and said,

114
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:13,300
Greetings, favored woman, the Lord is with you.

115
00:09:15,140 --> 00:09:19,180
Confused and disturbed, Mary tried to think what the angel could mean.

116
00:09:19,860 --> 00:09:26,260
Don't be frightened, Mary, the angel told her, for God has decided to bless you.

117
00:09:27,780 --> 00:09:32,060
You will become pregnant and have a son, and you are to name him Jesus.

118
00:09:33,490 --> 00:09:37,630
He will be very great and will be called the Son of the Most High,

119
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:41,250
and the Lord will give him the throne of his ancestor David

120
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:44,410
and he will reign over Israel forever.

121
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:47,170
His kingdom will never end.

122
00:09:48,940 --> 00:09:50,080
Mary asked the angel,

123
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:53,160
But how can I have a baby? I am a virgin.

124
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:55,380
And the angel replied,

125
00:09:55,540 --> 00:09:58,040
The Holy Spirit will come upon you

126
00:09:58,040 --> 00:10:01,560
and the power of the Most High will overshadow you.

127
00:10:02,420 --> 00:10:05,600
So the baby born to you will be holy

128
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:08,060
and will be called the Son of God.

129
00:10:09,520 --> 00:10:14,040
What's more, your relative Elizabeth has become pregnant in her old age.

130
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:18,560
People used to say she was barren, but she's already in her sixth month,

131
00:10:18,900 --> 00:10:22,340
for nothing is impossible with God.

132
00:10:24,380 --> 00:10:27,940
And Mary responded, I am the Lord's servant,

133
00:10:27,940 --> 00:10:31,560
and I am willing to accept whatever he wants.

134
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,580
May everything you have said come true.

135
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:37,440
And then the angel left.

136
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:42,910
Mary, roughly 15 years old,

137
00:10:44,260 --> 00:10:47,780
a young woman living in a male-dominated culture in a small town,

138
00:10:47,880 --> 00:10:49,820
engaged to a man named Joseph.

139
00:10:51,820 --> 00:10:56,620
God was calling this teenager to be the mother of Jesus,

140
00:10:56,820 --> 00:10:59,000
the Savior of the world.

141
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:05,120
And not only that, she would be a mother before she was ever with her husband.

142
00:11:05,680 --> 00:11:08,180
Scandal. Ridicule.

143
00:11:08,180 --> 00:11:12,880
it wasn't going to be an easy road for Mary.

144
00:11:15,020 --> 00:11:19,080
Mary's dream, this reality that God was speaking to her

145
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:21,180
would involve some risk.

146
00:11:22,400 --> 00:11:24,340
In order to see God's dream fulfilled

147
00:11:24,340 --> 00:11:27,860
she would just have to get over her fear and discomfort

148
00:11:27,860 --> 00:11:32,700
and if I can use the words of Nike, just do it.

149
00:11:34,250 --> 00:11:37,320
She would have to just do it.

150
00:11:40,550 --> 00:11:42,470
God calls you to a new dream,

151
00:11:42,470 --> 00:11:46,670
a new adventure with Him, a new ministry we can learn from Mary.

152
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:55,290
You see, the call to just do it, number one, comes from someone who loves us.

153
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:57,800
Someone who loves us.

154
00:11:59,340 --> 00:12:04,060
When God calls you to dream big dreams and challenges you to grow,

155
00:12:04,340 --> 00:12:09,760
He's coming as one who loves us and is for us.

156
00:12:11,080 --> 00:12:13,320
Do you realize God is for you?

157
00:12:14,460 --> 00:12:16,260
He wants you to grow.

158
00:12:16,520 --> 00:12:17,800
He wants you to be the best.

159
00:12:18,080 --> 00:12:19,420
He is on your side.

160
00:12:19,500 --> 00:12:20,660
He is for you.

161
00:12:23,620 --> 00:12:25,700
Notice how he came to Mary through the angel.

162
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,920
Greetings, favored woman.

163
00:12:28,990 --> 00:12:31,190
The Lord is with you.

164
00:12:32,850 --> 00:12:33,990
Don't be frightened, Mary,

165
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:37,580
for God has decided to bless you.

166
00:12:40,890 --> 00:12:43,110
God might be calling Mary to a big dream,

167
00:12:43,110 --> 00:12:46,090
a big commitment, a life-changing experience,

168
00:12:46,310 --> 00:12:47,810
but he's going to do it, notice,

169
00:12:47,810 --> 00:12:50,930
with His blessing and His presence.

170
00:12:52,330 --> 00:12:55,330
He's not sticking her out there all alone,

171
00:12:56,420 --> 00:13:00,020
but with His blessing and presence together.

172
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:03,000
The one who calls us, friends,

173
00:13:04,020 --> 00:13:05,660
outside of our comfort zones

174
00:13:05,660 --> 00:13:06,900
to dream His dreams

175
00:13:06,900 --> 00:13:09,340
and to accomplish the things He has for us.

176
00:13:09,340 --> 00:13:11,960
He loves us and is with us.

177
00:13:12,620 --> 00:13:14,380
Presence and blessing.

178
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:16,240
Do you believe it, church?

179
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:19,780
We can hear it, but do we believe it, church?

180
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:21,220
I hope so.

181
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:29,230
Number two, the call to just do it comes for a noble purpose.

182
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:36,460
When the angel appeared to Mary, the plan was being put into action.

183
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:42,620
And Jesus, her son, would be called great and would be called the Son of the Most High.

184
00:13:43,470 --> 00:13:51,610
Mary was being drawn into this divine drama where God is working in history to bring about his conclusion.

185
00:13:51,610 --> 00:13:57,210
And that conclusion involves sending Jesus to provide for our salvation.

186
00:13:58,230 --> 00:14:05,650
That conclusion involves our participation in growing the kingdom of God with our spiritual gifts.

187
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:12,470
God wants to use you to build the kingdom of God.

188
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:19,480
And he puts big dreams in our heads sometimes to accomplish those purposes.

189
00:14:20,320 --> 00:14:24,240
God is not asking you to risk for the risk itself.

190
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:30,620
For the sake of risk, He's not asking you to do it to impress Him or to impress others.

191
00:14:30,620 --> 00:14:36,660
He's asking you to just do it because He's calling you to a divine purpose,

192
00:14:36,980 --> 00:14:41,980
for a noble purpose, for a higher calling.

193
00:14:43,980 --> 00:14:46,440
Mary was called to bear the Son of God.

194
00:14:48,250 --> 00:14:53,930
Mary was called to endure the ridicule of a pregnancy before she was married.

195
00:14:55,340 --> 00:14:58,800
Mary was called to raise the child prodigy known as Jesus.

196
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:04,460
Mary was called to witness the bloody death of her son on the cross.

197
00:15:08,420 --> 00:15:11,340
But she was called for a noble purpose.

198
00:15:13,130 --> 00:15:16,510
She was called to dreams larger than her own.

199
00:15:16,510 --> 00:15:22,290
She was called out of her comfort zone of staying in this small town of Nazareth in Galilee

200
00:15:22,290 --> 00:15:25,570
for a larger purpose for the kingdom of God.

201
00:15:26,820 --> 00:15:27,820
Noble purpose.

202
00:15:31,620 --> 00:15:34,240
How do you know God's dreams for your own life?

203
00:15:36,360 --> 00:15:38,600
And I like what theologian Frederick Buechner said.

204
00:15:38,680 --> 00:15:47,780
He said, God's call to our lives is at the place where my gifts intersect with the needs of humanity.

205
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:51,980
where God can use you to meet needs

206
00:15:51,980 --> 00:15:53,660
and build the kingdom of God.

207
00:15:56,820 --> 00:15:58,220
You see, God's dream for us

208
00:15:58,220 --> 00:16:01,920
always involves serving the kingdom and others.

209
00:16:05,420 --> 00:16:07,080
When you come back next Sunday night,

210
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:10,600
when you come and we celebrate the Lord

211
00:16:10,600 --> 00:16:13,180
in worship and in communion,

212
00:16:14,100 --> 00:16:16,420
when you see those baptisms that night,

213
00:16:16,480 --> 00:16:19,820
when you see the representation of lives changed,

214
00:16:19,820 --> 00:16:21,160
you will say to yourself,

215
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:23,540
whatever we're doing for the kingdom of God,

216
00:16:23,540 --> 00:16:27,730
It is so worth it to see these lives changed.

217
00:16:30,140 --> 00:16:34,600
Lives in this very room are changed because many of you have dreamed dreams

218
00:16:34,600 --> 00:16:37,040
and gone and stretched outside of yourselves,

219
00:16:37,320 --> 00:16:41,000
and others have found Jesus Christ because of what you have done.

220
00:16:43,030 --> 00:16:46,670
He calls us to higher purposes, for noble purpose,

221
00:16:47,630 --> 00:16:49,710
to develop and grow the kingdom of God.

222
00:16:50,450 --> 00:16:53,370
There's nothing like it anywhere in the world.

223
00:16:53,790 --> 00:16:57,100
And there's nothing like stepping out of the comfort zone

224
00:16:57,100 --> 00:17:01,560
and having God catch you and meet you there.

225
00:17:03,450 --> 00:17:04,830
He calls us to a higher purpose.

226
00:17:04,950 --> 00:17:12,810
Number three, God calls us just to do it, and it requires a response.

227
00:17:15,460 --> 00:17:20,150
When God gets a hold of our lives, we have to respond.

228
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:26,740
A friend of mine once remarked offhandedly, and I made a mental note all these years,

229
00:17:26,740 --> 00:17:32,160
she said, you know, God is like a holy disruption in our lives.

230
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,420
Isn't that true?

231
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:37,490
He's a holy disruption.

232
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:43,370
You're planning your life and things are going safe and secure and then God intersects and

233
00:17:43,370 --> 00:17:49,920
things get a little out of control because you're out of your zone, but it's the only

234
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:50,560
way to live.

235
00:17:53,180 --> 00:17:56,380
When the angel spoke to Mary, she had to do something.

236
00:17:57,100 --> 00:17:58,280
She had to respond.

237
00:18:00,490 --> 00:18:01,510
She had to trust God.

238
00:18:02,620 --> 00:18:07,260
She had to leave her comfort zone, let God use her to change the world.

239
00:18:11,320 --> 00:18:15,020
Max Dupree, one of my favorite authors, says in this book, Leading Without Power,

240
00:18:16,950 --> 00:18:22,530
he says, by avoiding risk, we really risk what's most important in life,

241
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:29,260
reaching toward growth, our potential, and a true contribution towards the common good.

242
00:18:30,720 --> 00:18:34,180
By averting risk, we avoid those great challenges.

243
00:18:34,920 --> 00:18:40,250
Friends, if you sense God calling you to a dream, don't back away.

244
